# Pull Request Template Requirements

When creating a pull request (using `gh pr create`), follow the body structure in [`.github/pull_request_template.md`](../../.github/pull_request_template.md). Repository workflow rules are in [`.github/AGENTS.md`](../../.github/AGENTS.md); treat those as authoritative for PR operations.

- Keep **all section headings** from the template.
- Fill in **applicable** sections with concrete content; for sections that do not apply, use `N/A` (see `.github/AGENTS.md`).

## Sections (align with the template)

1. **Type of Change**: Check the box(es) that match the change. Prefer a single primary category; if the PR mixes types, pick the dominant one or note the mix briefly in **Summary** or **Additional Notes** (team convention).
2. **Related Issues**: Link related issue numbers (e.g., `Closes #123`).
3. **Summary of Changes**: Describe what changed and why (typically a short paragraph).
4. **Checklist**: Check all items that apply; `make pre-commit` must be checked when you are submitting the PR.
5. **Impact**: Check applicable boxes. If nothing applies, you may leave them unchecked and state **no breaking changes** or `N/A` in **Additional Notes**, as appropriate.
6. **Additional Notes**: Testing steps, deployment notes, or `N/A` when there is nothing extra.

## Example

```markdown
## Type of Change
- [ ] New Feature
- [x] Bug Fix
- [ ] Documentation

## Related Issues
Closes #2036

## Summary of Changes
Fixed anonymous access being denied when no PublicAccessBlock configuration exists.
`get_public_access_block_config` returning `ConfigNotFound` was incorrectly treated
as an access denial. Now it is handled as "no restrictions" per AWS S3 semantics.

## Checklist
- [x] I have read and followed the CONTRIBUTING.md guidelines
- [x] Passed `make pre-commit`
- [x] Added/updated necessary tests
- [ ] Documentation updated (if needed)
- [ ] CI/CD passed (if applicable)

## Impact
- [ ] Breaking change (compatibility)
- [ ] Requires doc/config/deployment update

## Additional Notes
Workaround for users who cannot upgrade: run `put-public-access-block` with all
options set to false on affected buckets.
```
